docs.abstract: After months of sheltering at home, 18 cohabitants on what so much togetherness has wrought.
docs.snippet: After months of sheltering at home, 18 cohabitants on what so much togetherness has wrought.
docs.lead_paragraph: It doesn’t take a Modern Love column to tell you that relationships can flourish — or wither — in times of stress. Add months of isolation, the physical and emotional toll of a pandemic, followed by global protests, and this period we’re living through has the capacity to reshape relationships on a broad scale.

byline.original: By Jessica Bennett, Daniel Jones, Miya Lee and Anya Strzemien

docs.abstract: Mason James Lira, 26, who shot a deputy in the face outside a police station in Paso Robles, Calif., early Wednesday, was surrounded by officers in a vineyard on Thursday, the authorities said.
docs.snippet: Mason James Lira, 26, who shot a deputy in the face outside a police station in Paso Robles, Calif., early Wednesday, was surrounded by officers in a vineyard on Thursday, the authorities said.
docs.lead_paragraph: A man who ambushed a sheriff’s deputy on Wednesday in Paso Robles, Calif., was killed on Thursday after a two-hour standoff during which three law enforcement officers were wounded when they surrounded him in a vineyard, the authorities said.

headline.main: Ambush Suspect Is Killed After Wounding 3 Officers in a Standoff, Sheriff Says

docs.abstract: Shows of support from Facebook, Twitter and YouTube don’t address the way those platforms have been weaponized by racists and partisan provocateurs.
docs.snippet: Shows of support from Facebook, Twitter and YouTube don’t address the way those platforms have been weaponized by racists and partisan provocateurs.
docs.lead_paragraph: Several weeks ago, as protests erupted across the nation in response to the police killing of George Floyd, Mark Zuckerberg wrote a long and heartfelt post on his Facebook page, denouncing racial bias and proclaiming that “black lives matter.” Mr. Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, also announced that the company would donate $10 million to racial justice organizations.

headline.main: Social Media Giants Support Racial Justice. Their Products Undermine It.
headline.print_headline: Platforms Denounce Racism That Thrives There

docs.abstract: HBO’s noir prequel has panache and a fine star performance, but it doesn’t entirely make the case for itself.
docs.snippet: HBO’s noir prequel has panache and a fine star performance, but it doesn’t entirely make the case for itself.
docs.lead_paragraph: I would not have expected “Perry Mason” to have any special relevance in the year 2020. The new HBO serial, set in 1931, based on a nearly nine-decade-old Erle Stanley Gardner book series that inspired a classic TV courtroom drama in 1957, is at first blush one more gritty pay-cable bummer about a tormented male antihero and the tough fellas and woeful dames who surround him.

headline.main: Review: ‘Perry Mason’ Returns, Hard-Boiled and Warmed Over
headline.print_headline: At Least the Gritty Streets Are Pretty
